⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Brass Tripod
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Brass Tripod:N1:1cc675⟧

WHO   — The Brass Tripod — the rite of vision
WHAT  — The night rite of vision he describes in his Preface — the brass tripod, the bowl of water, the divine fire said to move the prophet's hand — and the cryptic verse it produced, the most enduring book of prophecy ever written.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because he believed a divine fire could show a man the shape of things to come; because to speak it plainly was to risk the Inquisition, so it had to be veiled; because a prophecy obscure enough can never quite be proven wrong.
HOW   — By judicial astrology and the night rite of the brass tripod and the bowl of water, after the ancient Branchus and Apollo oracle — scrying by flame and water and a subtle spirit; and by a verse so allusive — French, Latin, anagram, omen — that it bends to any age that reads it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I sat before the brass and the water in the dark, and wrote what the fire showed me — in riddles, so that it could be read forever, and proven never.

spoken token : kryk-stein-virn   ·   hex : 1cc675
